BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:H34zicdxvzXfYCCULqyqp
SUMMARY:Toddler Music and Movement with ILS
DTSTAMP:20260307T065916Z
DTSTART:20260307T100000Z
DESCRIPTION:New 6-Week Music & Movement Session starts today! \\nOur Toddle
	r Music and Movement class is more than singing and dancing—it’s an intera
	ctive music class where children learn to feel music in their bodies. Over
	 six weeks\\\, we’ll explore percussion\\\, echoing and sequencing\\\, cou
	nting and marching\\\, ear training\\\, and early piano sounds. Some class
	es will feature percussion instruments\\\, while others include guitar or 
	ukulele\\\, and drums. \\nWith their caregivers\\\, children will learn to
	 find the beat\\\, move their feet\\\, and build early music foundations t
	hrough joyful routine and repetition. Regular attendance is encouraged so 
	kids can settle into the rhythm and grow with confidence. \\nA wonderful f
	irst step into music learning for young children. \\nLearn more and regist
	er here.\n\nhttps://myballard.com/event/toddler-music-and-movement-with-il
	s/\n\nFrom My Ballard
URL:https://myballard.com/event/toddler-music-and-movement-with-ils/
LOCATION:Illumination Learning Studio – Greenwood\\\, 7720 Greenwood Ave N\
	\\, Seattle\\\, WA\\\, 98103\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:myballard
CATEGORIES:My Ballard
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:n1XHyJ6bu3DvM2zrTlFH3
SUMMARY:Stained Glass Class: All Seeing Eye
DTSTAMP:20260307T065916Z
DTSTART:20260307T100000Z
DESCRIPTION:In this 3 hour class\\\, you will learn how to use the Tiffany 
	method of foiling\\\, gain guided experience with soldering technique\\\, 
	learn how to frame with lead came\\\, and how to properly clean and polish
	 stained glass. Each student will receive and work with a pre-cut and grou
	nd glass kit of the design pictured. All materials are included. \\nAt the
	 beginning of class\\\, we will cover best safety practices working with s
	tained glass\\\, and briefly cover the tools and materials you will be usi
	ng before diving in.\n\nhttps://myballard.com/event/stained-glass-class-al
	l-seeing-eye/\n\nFrom My Ballard
URL:https://myballard.com/event/stained-glass-class-all-seeing-eye/
