BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:zjAAFzmZPnvPFbMV4-rdb
SUMMARY:Origins
DTSTAMP:20260307T065916Z
DTSTART:20260307T140000Z
DESCRIPTION:Program:\\nCindy Cox*+ – Dreaming a world’s edge\\nRobert Schum
	ann – Piano Concerto in A minor\\\, Op. 54\\\, I. Allegro affettuoso\\n202
	5 Concerto Competition Winner: Isabel Yang\\\, Piano\\nFelix Mendelssohn –
	 Symphony No. 1 \\nJoin NOCCO for a vibrant evening of orchestral discover
	y and youthful brilliance. The concert opens with Cindy Cox’s Dreaming a w
	orld’s edge\\\, a richly textured and imaginative soundscape that explores
	 the boundaries between the real and the surreal. Next\\\, they spotlight 
	the rising talent of tomorrow with a performance by NOCCO’s 2025 Concerto 
	Competition Winner — an exciting opportunity to witness a gifted young sol
	oist take center stage. The evening concludes with the energetic charm and
	 classical elegance of Felix Mendelssohn’s Symphony No. 1\\\, a remarkable
	 early work that showcases the composer’s precocious genius. This program 
	promises inspiration\\\, innovation\\\, and unforgettable music-making. \\
	n*POC or Woman Composer\\n+Living Composer \\n\\nEvents are offered for in
	formational\\\, entertainment\\\, and educational purposes only. Read Town
	 Hall’s Program Content Policy.\n\nhttps://townhallseattle.org/event/origi
	ns/\n\nFrom Town Hall Seattle
URL:https://townhallseattle.org/event/origins/
LOCATION:The Great Hall\\\, 1119 Eighth Avenue (enter on Eighth Avenue)\\\,
	 Seattle\\\, 98101\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:town-hall-seattle
CATEGORIES:Town Hall Seattle
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:FZoFPPJYrCbf0y7knv6oc
SUMMARY:Crochet Class: Book Cover Granny Squares
DTSTAMP:20260307T065916Z
DTSTART:20260307T150000Z
DESCRIPTION:While this class is beginner-friendly\\\, knowing the basics li
	ke a slip knot\\\, single crochet\\\, and double crochet will be necessary
	 for this project. If you would like to join and don’t have these skills y
	et check out my beginner crochet class at Swoon City or find some good tut
	orials on YouTube. I taught myself to crochet before the Internet existed 
	and have all the faith you can learn too! \\nWe will make a classic granny
	 square in this class\\\, but there are many variations of granny squares.
	 Granny squares can create bags\\\, blankets\\\, sweaters\\\, and more! We
	 will focus on making granny squares that resemble book covers. You can us
	e the cover colors or even replicate the parts of the cover design! \\nThi
	s class will include all the colors necessary to create your book-themed g
	ranny square\\\, a guide to making granny squares\\\, and a hook. Please p
	rovide a picture of the cover you are looking to create to info@swoon.city
	 after booking\n\nhttps://myballard.com/event/crochet-class-book-cover-gra
	nny-squares/\n\nFrom My Ballard
URL:https://myballard.com/event/crochet-class-book-cover-granny-squares/
